3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EAirport%20workers%20in%20Phoenix%2C%20Charlotte%20describe%20dangerous%20conditions%20during%20extreme%20heat.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThey%20joined%20fast-food%20and%20farm%20workers%20this%20week%20in%20demanding%20employers%20provide%20water%2C%20AC%2C%20and%20rest.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EFive%20states%20and%20some%20cities%20have%20heat%20protection%20policies%2C%20but%20enforcement%20is%20inconsistent.%20%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ECecilia%20Ortiz%20walks%2010%20to%2015%20miles%20a%20day%20for%20her%20job%20at%20Phoenix%20Sky%20Harbor%20International%20Airport%2C%20pushing%20people%20in%20wheelchairs%20to%20their%20gates%20and%20carrying%20luggage.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20loves%20her%20job%2C%20but%20it%20comes%20with%20risks%2C%20especially%20when%20temperatures%20reach%20triple%20digits%20for%20months%20in%20Phoenix.%20Ortiz%20said%20she%20sweats%20through%20her%20thick%20polyester%20uniform%20on%20jet%20bridges%20that%20aren't%20always%20air-conditioned.%20Access%20to%20cold%20water%20and%20rest%20breaks%20aren't%20guaranteed.%20Some%20of%20her%20colleagues%20who%20clean%20airplane%20cabins%2C%20transport%20luggage%20on%20the%20tarmac%2C%20or%20work%20as%20curbside%20agents%20have%20reported%20dizziness%2C%20nausea%2C%20and%20vomiting%20on%20the%20job%20%E2%80%94%20symptoms%20of%20heat%20exhaustion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOrtiz%20this%20week%20is%20joining%20workers%20in%20the%20airline%2C%20fast-food%2C%20and%20farming%20sectors%20in%2013%20cities%20to%20demand%20that%20employers%20provide%20education%20and%20training%20about%20the%20symptoms%20of%20heat%20exhaustion%2C%20develop%20a%20plan%20of%20action%20for%20getting%20employees%20medical%20attention%2C%20and%20ensure%20that%20employees%20have%20access%20to%20water%2C%20shade%2C%20air%20conditioning%2C%20and%20rest%20breaks.%20On%20Tuesday%20there%20were%20demonstrations%20at%20airports%20in%20Phoenix%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.qcnews.com%2Fcharlotte%2Fservice-workers-at-charlotte-airport-protest-for-heat-protection%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECharlotte%2C%20North%20Carolina%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20on%20Thursday%20workers%20plan%20to%20take%20a%20coordinated%20drink%20of%20water%20and%20share%20it%20across%20social%20media.%20Several%20labor%20unions%20are%20organizing%20the%20actions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EScorching%20heat%20is%20becoming%20more%20common%20in%20the%20US%20and%20around%20the%20world.%20Scientists%20have%20found%20that%20the%20climate%20crisis%20is%20causing%20more%20frequent%2C%20intense%2C%20and%20longer-lasting%20heat%20waves.%20Federal%20data%20indicates%20that%20each%20year%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bls.gov%2Fopub%2Fted%2F2023%2F36-work-related-deaths-due-to-environmental-heat-exposure-in-2021.htm%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edozens%20of%20workers%20in%20the%20US%20die%20from%20heat%20exposure%3C%2Fa%3E.%20This%20summer%2C%20a%20sanitation%20worker%20for%20the%20city%20of%20Baltimore%20died%20from%20hyperthermia%2C%20or%20overheating%2C%20and%20the%20Occupational%20Safety%20and%20Health%20Administration%20is%20investigating%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.usatoday.com%2Fstory%2Fnews%2Fnation%2F2024%2F07%2F15%2Fusps-worker-heat-stroke-death-wendy-johnson%2F74414304007%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewhether%20a%20postal%20worker's%20death%20in%20North%20Carolina%20was%20related%20to%20the%20heat%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20no%20national%20standards%20to%20protect%20indoor%20and%20outdoor%20workers.%20The%20Biden%20administration%20in%20July%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbidens-heat-standards-workers-water-shade-rest-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eproposed%20rules%20for%20employers%20with%20workers%20exposed%20to%20temperatures%20of%2080%20degrees%20Fahrenheit%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20higher%2C%20but%20it%20could%20be%20years%20before%20they%20take%20effect.%20The%20rules%20could%20also%20be%20scrapped%20if%20former%20President%20Donald%20Trump%20wins%20the%20election%20in%20November.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20states%20and%20cities%20have%20enacted%20their%20own%20policies%2C%20including%20California%20and%20Phoenix.%20This%20fall%20Maryland%20is%20expected%20to%20become%20the%20sixth%20state%20to%20adopt%20heat%20protections%20for%20workers.%20Meanwhile%2C%20Florida%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftexas-extreme-heat-construction-crews-lose-breaks-water-2023-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETexas%20have%20blocked%20such%20protections%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20the%20local%20level.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Phoenix%20City%20Council%20in%20April%20unanimously%20passed%20an%20ordinance%20requiring%20all%20city%20contractors%20and%20subcontractors%20to%20develop%20heat-safety%20plans%20for%20outdoor%20workers%2C%20including%20at%20construction%20sites%20and%20airports.%20The%20ordinance%20also%20requires%20access%20to%20rest%2C%20shade%2C%20water%2C%20and%20air%20conditioning.%20By%202025%2C%20closed-cab%20vehicles%2C%20like%20those%20that%20move%20airport%20baggage%2C%20must%20have%20AC.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOrtiz%20described%20the%20ordinance%20as%20a%20big%20win%20but%20said%20she%20still%20hadn't%20seen%20her%20employer%2C%20Prospect%20Airport%20Services%2C%20make%20changes.%20The%20company%20has%20more%20than%208%2C500%20employees%20at%2026%20airports%20around%20the%20US%20and%20has%20contracts%20with%20airlines%20to%20provide%20passenger%20services%2C%20baggage%20handlers%2C%20and%20gate%20agents.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20ordinance%20took%20effect%20in%20April%2C%20and%20we're%20in%20August%20now%2C%20still%20fighting%20for%20our%20basic%20human%20rights%20to%20a%20break%20and%20water%2C%26quot%3B%20Ortiz%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20and%20other%20airport%20contract%20workers%20tried%20to%20deliver%20a%20copy%20of%20the%20Phoenix%20ordinance%20to%20their%20supervisor%20on%20Tuesday%2C%20but%20he%20wouldn't%20leave%20his%20office%2C%20Ortiz%20said.%20Last%20August%2C%20Ortiz%20and%2010%20other%20employees%20filed%20a%20complaint%20with%20Arizona's%20occupational-safety%20authorities%2C%20who%20opened%20an%20investigation%20and%20conducted%20an%20on-site%20inspection%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Fclimate-environment%2F2023%2F09%2F06%2Fphoenix-excessive-heat-airport-workers%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Washington%20Post%20reported%3C%2Fa%3E.%20A%20spokesman%20for%20the%20Arizona%20Division%20of%20Occupational%20Safety%20and%20Health%20told%20Business%20Insider%20they%20could%20not%20immediately%20provide%20information%20about%20that%20investigation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnifi%20Aviation%2C%20the%20parent%20company%20of%20Prospect%20Airport%20Services%2C%20told%20BI%20in%20a%20statement%20that%20it%20had%20a%20heat-illness-prevention%20program%20that%20takes%20effect%20when%20temperatures%20exceed%2080%20degrees%2C%20adding%20that%20managers%20are%20encouraged%20to%20continuously%20check%20for%20signs%20of%20heat%20stress%20or%20illness%20among%20employees.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAll%20outdoor%20workers%20are%20provided%20with%20extra%20breaks%2C%20quick%20access%20to%20unlimited%20water%2C%20Gatorade%2C%20cooling%20towels%20and%20popsicles%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20company%20said.%20%26quot%3BWhen%20possible%2C%20misting%20stations%20are%20also%20set%20up%20at%20the%20airports%20in%20partnership%20with%20airport%20or%20airline%20officials.%20Employees%20are%20also%20told%20not%20to%20sit%20or%20loiter%20in%20jet%20bridges%20for%20their%20own%20safety%20and%20that%20of%20those%20around%20them.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20California%2C%20farm%20workers%20are%20especially%20vulnerable%20to%20extreme%20heat.%20Lourdes%20Cardenas%20is%20a%20farm%20worker%20who%20lives%20in%20Fresno%2C%20California%2C%20where%20it%20has%20reached%20upward%20of%20105%20degrees%20Fahrenheit%20this%20summer.%20She%20said%20even%20though%20the%20state%20has%20a%20heat%20protection%20law%2C%20companies%20don't%20always%20follow%20it.%20Last%20summer%2C%20while%20working%20in%20tomato%20fields%20without%20shade%2C%20she%20had%20a%20headache%20and%20vomited.%20She%20had%20to%20drive%20herself%20home%20to%20rest.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMany%20workers%20don't%20say%20anything%20when%20they%20feel%20bad%20because%20they%20are%20afraid%20they%20will%20be%20fired%2C%20or%20because%20they%20earn%20so%20little%20that%20they%20feel%20they%20have%20to%20take%20risks%20to%20get%20a%20paycheck%2C%26quot%3B%20Cardenas%20said%20during%20a%20press%20conference%20on%20Monday%20hosted%20by%20labor%20unions%2C%20including%20United%20Farm%20Workers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFast-food%20workers%20at%20Waffle%20House%20and%20Starbucks%20told%20BI%20that%20AC%20units%20at%20some%20locations%20were%20broken%20for%20weeks%20last%20summer%2C%20causing%20the%20restaurants%20to%20be%20hotter%20than%2080%20degrees.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20know%20that%20the%20planet%20is%20getting%20hotter%20and%20hotter%20every%20year%2C%20and%20we're%20seeing%20skyrocketing%20conditions%20for%20workers%20that%20people%20may%20not%20always%20think%20of%20when%20they%20think%20about%20the%20heat%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20April%20Verrett%2C%20the%20president%20of%20the%20Service%20Employees%20International%20Union%2C%20which%20is%20helping%20organize%20this%20week's%20rallies.%20%26quot%3BFolks%20on%20jet%20bridges%20or%20in%20the%20kitchen%2C%20where%20temperatures%20can%20exceed%20110%20degrees%20%E2%80%94%20they're%20making%20these%20demands%20that%20it's%20time%20for%20employers%20to%20act%20now.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fairport-farm-fast-food-workers-rally-heat-protections-phoenix-charlotte-2024-8%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1723719601000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66bd20c25da406397bf6132a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https