t%20that%2C%20you%20will%20come%20out%20of%20that%20a%20stronger%20person%2C%20whereas%20there%20will%20be%20other%20companies%20where%20if%20you%20show%20emotions%2C%20you're%20penalized%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%224dc88e05-f0a6-47f0-9d66-a81bdeaa974b%5C%22%3EHow%20crying%20at%20work%20is%20viewed%20depends%20on%20several%20factors%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%202018%20survey%20found%20that%2031%25%20of%20workers%20and%2030%25%20of%202%2C200%20CFOs%20who%20were%20also%20questioned%20said%20that%20crying%20at%20work%20should%20not%20negatively%20affect%20someone's%20standing%20at%20work%20and%20shows%20you're%20human.%20However%2C%2044%25%20of%20CFOs%20and%2038%25%20of%20workers%20agreed%20that%20crying%20at%20work%20was%20OK%20%26quot%3Bfrom%20time%20to%20time%2C%26quot%3B%20but%20doing%20it%20too%20often%20could%20undermine%20your%20prospects.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20reason%20you're%20crying%20will%20also%20influence%20others'%20perception%20of%20it%2C%20Weaven%20said.%20Most%20people%20will%20understand%20crying%20over%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgrief-emotional-breakdown-at-work-death-of-parent-boss-reaction-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebereavement%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20but%20fewer%20will%20sympathize%20with%20crying%20about%20a%20work-related%20problem.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWeaven%20said%20that%20crying%20doesn't%20have%20to%20be%20seen%20as%20negative%2C%20as%20it's%20not%20unusual%20for%20employees%20to%20cry%20because%20they're%20passionate%20and%20want%20to%20do%20a%20good%20job.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI've%20seen%20situations%20where%20people%20have%20been%20pulled%20up%20on%20their%20performance%2C%20and%20they've%20got%20upset%20because%20they%20want%20to%20do%20their%20best.%20When%20people%20care%20about%20the%20work%2C%20emotions%20can%20come%20out%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%202016%20Harvard%20Business%20School%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hbs.edu%2