g.%20The%20employee%20kept%20apologizing%20for%20being%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fthings-never-do-work-hr-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eunprofessional%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%26quot%3BI%20thought%20she%20shouldn't%20have%20to%20apologize.%20She'd%20just%20had%20really%20big%20news%20and%20it%20was%20only%20me%20and%20her%20in%20the%20office%2C%26quot%3B%20Weaven%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20do%20find%20yourself%20welling%20up%20with%20a%20larger%20group%2C%20such%20as%20a%20big%20meeting%2C%20Weaven%20advised%20trying%20to%20leave%20the%20room%20if%20you%20can.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhatever%20the%20specific%20situation%2C%20Weaven%20said%20it's%20worth%20acknowledging%20the%20reaction%20with%20colleagues%20if%20you%20are%20concerned%20about%20how%20they%20perceived%20it.%20For%20example%2C%20if%20it%20was%20with%20your%20manager%2C%20you%20could%20discuss%20it%20with%20them%20and%20explain%20why%20you%20cried.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20more%20they%20know%20you%20and%20the%20way%20that%20you%20work%2C%20the%20better%20they're%20going%20to%20be%20able%20to%20manage%20you%2C%26quot%3B%20Weaven%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcrying-at-work-ok-hr-expert-advice-2024-8%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1723716866000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66bcdce45da406397bf5eb17%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcrying-at-work-ok-hr-expert-advice-2024-8%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Crying%20at%20work%20is%20pretty%20normal%2C%20surveys%20have%20shown.%20Whether%20it's%20bad%20or%20okay%20depends%20on%20your%20office%20culture.%20An%20HR%20expert%20explains%20how%20to%20handle%20it.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Isabelle%20Aron)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A14%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcrying-