%20at%20my%20retirement%20age%20of%2065%20and%20was%20to%20go%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fretirement-social-security-peak-boomer-alaska-medical-expenses-financial-insecurity-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESocial%20Security%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20I%20had%20done%20some%20research%20and%20found%20that%20Guatemala%20was%20probably%20one%20of%20the%20cheapest%20options%20available%20for%20people%20on%20retirement%20income.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EZimmerman%20went%20to%20Guatemala%20for%20two%20weeks%20to%20scope%20it%20out%2C%20first%20settling%20in%20the%20village%20of%20San%20Marcos%20La%20Laguna%20on%20the%20shores%20of%20Lake%20Atitl%C3%A1n.%20They%20drove%20their%20truck%20through%20Mexico%20to%20the%20town%20of%20about%202%2C200%20people%20in%20one%20of%20the%20more%20touristy%20parts%20of%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20towns%20along%20the%20lake%20struck%20him%20for%20their%20colorful%20buildings%2C%20tiny%20coffee%20shops%20built%20within%20the%20jungle%2C%20cultural%20diversity%2C%20and%20low%20prices.%20He%20said%20the%20area%20was%20also%20a%20popular%20site%20for%20religious%20offerings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BLake%20Atitl%C3%A1n%20has%20a%20history%20of%20being%20a%20place%20that%20not%20a%20lot%20of%20people%20know%20about%2C%20but%20people%20find%20a%20real%20eye-opening%20place%2C%26quot%3B%20Zimmerman%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe%20didn't%20have%20any%20expectations%20of%20what%20we%20would%20confront%20there.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2257ed3e06-33aa-4ef1-b99a-ad6dcd1c62f4%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ELiving%20in%20Guatemala%3A%20Pros%20and%20cons%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20rented%20a%20house%20they%20thought%20was%20unsteady%20and%20could%20not%20withstand%20an%20earthquake%20if%20it%20hit%20their%20area.%20Part%20of%20their%20home%20was%20open%20to%20the%20street%2C%20so%20he%20said%20they%20would%20smell%20exhaust%20or%20overhear%20street%20conversations%20constantly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20moved%20to%20Panajachel%2C%20a%20town%20of%20about%2011%2C000%20on%20the%20northeast%20side%20of%20the%20lake.%20The%20town%20boasted%20many%20craftsmen%20selling%20clothing%20and%20bags%2C%20coffee%20shops%20run%20by%20expats%2C%20and%20gorgeous%20lake%20views%2C%20surrounded%20by%20three%20volcanoes.%20The%20towns%20surrounding%20the%20lake%20are%20%26quot%3Breal%20happening%20spots%20for%20young%20people%2C%26quot%3B%20Zimmerman%20said%2C%20noting%20that%20bars%20and%20restaurants%20were%20often%20full%20in%20the%20evenings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223264%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Panajachel%20view%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66bd0fa45da406397bf60a66%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222448%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EViews%20of%20Lake%20Atitl%C3%A1n%20from%20Panajachel.%3Cp%3ERobert%20Zimmerman%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20loved%20visiting%20many%20of%20Guatemala's%20historic%20sites%2C%20such%20as%20the%20colonial%20buildings%20of%20Quetzaltenango%20and%20the%20Baroque%20architecture%20of%20Antigua%20Guatemala.%20Rents%20in%20these%20cities%20were%20outside%20their%20budgets%2C%20Zimmerman%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPrices%20were%20affordable%20for%20housing%20and%20daily%20expenses%2C%20which%20they%20paid%20using%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fretirement-peak-boomer-alice-social-security-masters-degree-student-loans-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESocial%20Security%3C%2Fa%3E%20income.%20Zimmerman%20said%20they%20paid%20%24400%20a%20month%20for%20a%20furnished%20house%20with%20an%20American%20landlord%2C%20then%20rented%20a%20cabin%20surrounded%20by%20the%20jungle%20for%20about%20%24350%20a%20month.%20They%20also%20had%20a%20maid%20and%20a%20gardener%20at%20the%20home%2C%20which%20cost%20them%20about%20%2410%20a%20week.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETransportation%20on%20three-wheeled%20bikes%20cost%2060%20cents%20a%20ride%2C%20though%20Zimmerman%20said%20food%20costs%20were%20comparable%20to%20those%20in%20the%20US%2C%20given%20many%20products%20were%20imported.%20Going%20out%20to%20eat%2C%20though%2C%20was%20much%20cheaper%20%E2%80%94%20he%20recalled%20paying%2050%20cents%20for%20rice%20and%20beans%2C%20%241%20for%20pizza%2C%20%242.50%20for%20large%20breakfasts%2C%20and%20%242%20for%20beer%20at%20a%20bar.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20had%20their%20electric%20bill%20subsidized%2C%20so%20they%20paid%20just%20%2412%20a%20month.%20Their%20cable%20bill%20was%20about%20the%20same%20as%20the%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EZimmerman%20said%20they%20paid%20%2412%20for%20a%20US-trained%20doctor%20in%20their%20town%2C%20including%20for%20his%20wife's%20gallbladder%20surgery.%20He%20acknowledged%20there%20wasn't%20state-of-the-art%20healthcare%20in%20the%20town%2C%20though%20dental%20care%20was%20about%20equivalent%20to%20the%20US%20for%20half%20the%20price.%20He%20said%20his%20doctors%20would%20give%20them%20free%20medications.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20they%20found%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbiden-laws-us-infrastructure-invest-funding-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Einfrastructure%3C%2Fa%3E%20lacking.%20They%20never%20drank%20the%20tap%20water%2C%20as%20they%20said%20it%20came%20from%20a%20ditch%20that%20sometimes%20smelled%20like%20raw%20sewage.%20Zimmerman%20said%20he%20got%20sick%20a%20few%20times%20from%20eating%20food%20from%20street%20sellers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20often%20interacted%20with%20the%20locals%2C%20though%20he%20said%20his%20town%20attracted%20many%20US%20expats%2C%20meaning%20that%20most%20people%20he%20spoke%20with%20were%20not%20from%20Guatemala.%20Due%20to%20the%20large%20expat%20community%2C%20he%20didn't%20learn%20Spanish%20beyond%20a%20few%20common%20phrases.%20However%2C%20he%20acknowledged%20he%20never%20acclimated%20to%20the%20environment%20and%20that%20the%20language%20barrier%20hindered%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHis%20relationship%20with%20the%20area%20quickly%20soured%20when%20he%20realized%20that%20many%20locals%20shot%20fireworks%20%E2%80%94%20which%20he%20described%20as%20%26quot%3Bsmall%20bombs%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20randomly%20each%20day%20as%20late%20as%204%20a.m.%2C%20which%20affected%20his%20sleep%20schedule.%20He%20said%20he%20was%20met%20with%20vitriol%20when%20he%20issued%20noise%20complaints.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThough%20he%20respected%20the%20locals'%20cultural%20and%20religious%20traditions%2C%20he%20said%20he%20never%20got%20used%20to%20how%20religious%20his%20area%20was.%20He%20lived%20next%20to%20a%20church%2C%20noting%20the%20sermons%20were%20often%20blasted%20out%20onto%20the%20streets%20via%20speakers.%20He%20said%20traffic%20would%20often%20be%20disrupted%20during%20church%20services.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22c542dd74-612d-41a9-9d9b-f2b365878983%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EMoving%20back%20to%20the%20US%20%E2%80%94%20and%20paying%20more%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20lived%20in%20Guatemala%20during%20the%20Covid%20lockdowns%2C%20which%20restricted%20the%20hours%20businesses%20were%20open%20and%20when%20residents%20could%20leave%20their%20homes.%20By%20then%2C%20Zimmerman%20and%20his%20wife%20had%20wanted%20to%20leave%2C%20and%20they%20decided%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmoved-to-europe-from-us-regret-felt-homesick-misunderstood-lonely-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emove%20back%20to%20the%20US%3C%2Fa%3E%20during%20the%20Covid%20recovery%20period.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20bought%20an%20old%20Jeep%20and%20loaded%20it%20with%20their%20belongings%2C%20then%2C%20after%20some%20challenges%20at%20the%20border%2C%20drove%20through%20Mexico.%20They%20knew%20moving%20back%20to%20the%20US%20would%20be%20more%20expensive%2C%20though%20it%20was%20their%20only%20option%20given%20their%20finances.%20Zimmerman%20said%20they%20wanted%20to%20return%20to%20the%20comfort%20of%20the%20US%20for%20a%20few%20years%20before%20deciding%20whether%20or%20not%20to%20move%20abroad%20again.%20They%20also%20needed%20to%20pay%20a%20penalty%20for%20renewing%20their%20Medicare%20after%20dropping%20coverage%20when%20moving%20to%20Guatemala.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20they%20moved%20back%20to%20the%20US%2C%20Zimmerman%20estimated%20they%20had%20about%20%2450%2C000%20in%20the%20bank.%20He%20knew%20he%20had%20to%20return%20to%20work%2C%20so%20he%20studied%20a%20business%20intelligence%20tool%20to%20land%20a%20specialized%20position.%20However%2C%20he%20said%20he%20never%20became%20fully%20proficient%20and%20is%20considering%20working%20as%20a%20contractor.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20couldn't%20afford%20to%20move%20back%20to%20the%20Seattle%20area%2C%20so%20after%20some%20time%20at%20Zimmerman's%20sister's%20place%20in%20Las%20Vegas%2C%20they%20moved%20to%20Illinois%2C%20living%20in%20cities%20like%20Belleville%2C%20Peoria%2C%20and%20now%20Rockford%20%E2%80%94%20which%20has%20a%20cheaper%20cost%20of%20living%20with%20fewer%20property%20taxes.%20They%20lived%20off%20Social%20Security%20while%20Zimmerman%20searched%20for%20his%20next%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMost%20of%20the%20people%20I%20worked%20with%20in%20Seattle%20now%20have%20high-paying%20tech%20jobs%2C%20and%20I%20am%20unable%20to%20find%20equal%20work%20here%20in%20small-town%20Illinois%2C%26quot%3B%20Zimmerman%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EHave%20you%20recently%20left%20the%20United%20States%20for%20a%20new%20country%3F%20Reach%20out%20to%20this%20reporter%20at%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Ansheidlower%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3Ensheidlower%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fboomer-couple-couldnt-afford-retirement-moved-to-guatemala-social-security-2024-8%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1723715882000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22http