tion%20torching%20began.%20Over%20and%20over%20in%20the%20two-hour%2C%20seven-minute%20conversation%2C%20Trump%20trampled%20on%20the%20values%20that%20constructed%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-super-fired-up-help-biden-fight-climate-change-2021-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EMusk's%20brand%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20(%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-private-jet-carbon-footprint-climate-change-2023-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ewarranted%20or%20not%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E).%20When%20Trump%20claimed%20the%20biggest%20threat%20to%20humanity%20was%20not%20the%20climate%20crisis%20%E2%80%94%20partly%20because%20it%20would%20provide%20humans%20with%20more%20oceanfront%20property%20%E2%80%94%20Musk%20lamely%20muttered%20an%20%26quot%3BOK.%26quot%3B%20You%20would%20think%20the%20man%20who%20said%20citizens%20needed%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fenvironment%2F2016%2Fmay%2F05%2Felon-musk-we-need-a-revolt-against-the-fossil-fuel-industry%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eto%20%26quot%3Brevolt%26quot%3B%20against%20the%20fossil-fuel%20industry%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20and%20decried%20its%20government%20subsidies%20in%202016%20would%20have%20more%20to%20say%20about%20that.%20Instead%2C%20he%20asked%20listeners%20not%20to%20demonize%20the%20oil%20and%20gas%20industry%20and%20insisted%20that%20the%20climate%20could%20wait.%20It%20was%20only%20after%20about%201%20%C2%BD%20hours%20of%20Trump%20drilling%20into%20Musk%20with%20his%20now%20stale%2C%20unhinged%20xenophobic%20meanderings%20that%20Musk%20offered%20a%20flimsy%20defense%20of%20the%20reality%20of%20the%20climate%20emergency.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Tesla%2FSpaceX%2FX%20CEO%20was%20run%20roughshod%20on%20his%20core%20issue%2C%20and%20then%20Trump%20guided%20Musk%20down%20a%20rabbit%2