sa-astronaut-boeing-starliner-good-feeling-be-back-safe-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egood%20time%20on%20the%20ISS%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20that%20it%20%26quot%3Bfeels%20good%20to%20float%20around.%26quot%3B%20And%20Wilmore%20said%20he%20was%20%26quot%3B%3Cspan%3Eabsolutely%20confident%26quot%3B%20the%20Starliner%20will%20get%20them%20home%20safe.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20%3Cspan%3Eaccording%20to%20a%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftime.com%2F7010425%2Fstranded-astronauts-iss-butch-wilmore-suni-williams%2F%3Ffbclid%3DPAZXh0bgNhZW0CMTEAAab5hSFjSS_MKRavzBKd6lgzUtkNy4dr-RvR-hmqyEXBW4XjXdvKsllVzok_aem_LIAlK8spm2FkblPlW0QDKg%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ereport%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0by%20Time%20editor%20Jeffrey%20Kluger%2C%20who%20covers%20space%20and%20science%2C%20Wilmore%20is%20roughing%20it%20out%20during%20his%20stay.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWilmore%2C%20per%20Kluger%2C%20was%20prepared%20to%20rest%20in%20a%20sleeping%20bag%20in%20the%20Japanese%20Space%20Agency's%20Kibo%20module%20for%20eight%20days.%20But%20that%20trip%20on%20June%205%20has%20extended%20well%20beyond%20two%20months%2C%20and%20it%20may%20be%20February%202025%20when%20the%20astronauts%20are%20brought%20back%20to%20Earth.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nasa.gov%2Finternational-space-station%2Fspace-station-facts-and-figures%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENASA%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20ISS%20only%20has%20six%20private%20sleeping%20quarters.%20Time%20reported%20that%20each%20quarter%20has%20a%20sleeping%20bag%2C%20a%20storage%20area%20for%20snacks%20and%20personal%20belongings%2C%20and%20two%20laptops%20attached%20to%20the%20walls.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20Wilmore%20and%20Williams%20joined%20an%20international%20crew%20of%20seven%20people%20already%20at%20the%20ISS%20%E2%80%94%20so%20the%20sleep%20cabins%20were%20already%20at%20maximum%20capacity.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETime%20reported%20that%20Williams%20camps%20with%20one%20of%20the%20astronauts%20in%20a%20basic%20sleep%20module%20called%20the%20CASA%2C%20or%20Crew%20Alternate%20Sleep%20Accommodation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20Wilmore%20has%20been%20given%20a%20sleeping%20bag%20to%20rest%20in%2C%20out%20in%20the%20Japanese%20module.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKluger%20wrote%20that%20Williams%20joked%20to%20him%20in%20May%20before%20she%20left%20for%20space%2C%20saying%3A%20%26quot%3BButch%20is%20going%20to%20have%20to%20rough%20it%20a%20little%20bit.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20they're%20stuck%20in%20space%2C%20the%20duo%20has%20likely%20also%20started%20working%20odd%20jobs%20on%20the%20ISS%2C%20per%20Time.%20They%20began%20with%20mission%20goals%20for%20the%20short%20stint%20they%20initially%20planned%20to%20be%20on%2C%20like%20carrying%20out%20checks%20on%20the%20Starliner%20after%20its%20test%20flight.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBut%20they%20long%20since%20finished%20up%20that%20checklist%20and%20have%20instead%20been%20assisting%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20crew%20with%20science%20experiments%20and%20maintenance%20chores%2C%20including%20such%20unglamorous%20work%20as%20repairing%20a%20urine%20processing%20pump%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20Time%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20duo%20also%20packed%20a%20small%20selection%20of%20clothes%2C%20insufficient%20for%20a%20prolonged%20stay.%20But%20Time%20reported%20that%20a%20Northrop%20Grumman%20resupply%20spaceship%20delivered%20fresh%20clothes%20to%20both%20astronauts%20last%20week.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22c92f8e05-b076-4e75-a6b1-2f5f4c1188ab%5C%22%3EA%20waiting%20game%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20astronauts%20have%20now%20spent%20more%20than%2070%20days%20in%20the%20ISS%2C%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-nasa-taking-long-to-bring-boeing-astronauts-home-earth-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eno%20immediate%20end%20in%20sight.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20August%207%2C%20NASA%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5