2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EAir%20Force%20veteran%20began%20practicing%20as%20an%20orthodontist%20in%201990%20and%20raised%20three%20daughters%20in%20Texas.%20But%20over%20time%20he%20became%20concerned%20about%20the%20US%20financial%20system%2C%20even%20joining%20an%20advocacy%20group%20to%20educate%20voters%20about%20the%20ballooning%20national%20debt.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20then%20came%202008%20and%20its%20fiscal%20crisis.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNobody%20had%20their%20hand%20slapped.%20The%20only%20thing%20that%20was%20done%20was%20to%20print%20money%20and%20bail%20all%20the%20big%20boys%20out%2C%26quot%3B%20Karl%2C%20whose%20full%20name%20is%20known%20to%20Business%20Insider%20but%20withheld%20over%20privacy%20concerns%2C%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20finally%20decided%20that%20things%20were%20not%20going%20well%20in%20the%20United%20States%2C%20and%20I%20started%20looking%20for%20a%20place%2C%20what%20I%20would%20call%20a%20'bug-out'%20place%20for%20my%20children%20in%20case%20things%20didn't%20go%20well%20in%20the%20United%20States.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20year%20earlier%2C%20Karl's%20first%20wife%20had%20died.%20All%20of%20that%20led%20him%20to%20ponder%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fretired-boomer-moved-abroad-cost-living-mexico-cheaper-than-us-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eretiring%20abroad%3C%2Fa%3E.%20His%20goal%20for%20retirement%20was%20simply%20to%20read%20and%20write%20for%20his%20own%20education%2C%20poring%20over%20his%20collection%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eof%20books.%20The%20places%20that%20he%20had%20been%20eyeing%20didn't%20have%20good%20climates%20for%20books%2C%20though%2C%20so%20he%20fired%20up%20a%20simple%20Google%20search%3A%20%26quot%3BBest%20weather%20in%20the%20world.%26quot%3B%20That's%20how%20he%20chanced%20upon%20Cuenca%2C%20Ecuador.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20same%20time%2C%20Karl%20had%20met%20someone%3A%20Brenda%2C%20a%20medical%20technologist%20who%20was%20also%20pondering%20a%20retirement%20elsewhere.%20In%20Texas%2C%20Brenda%20found%20an%20environment%20heavy%20with%20tension%3A%20%26quot%3BEvery%20time%20I%20would%20go%20into%20a%20store%2C%20I%20get%20this%20feeling%20that%20everyone's%20stressed.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBrenda%20was%20also%20concerned%20about%20having%20a%20financially%20sustainable%20retirement%2C%20after%20buying%20a%20house%20in%202007%20and%20then%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fworldwide-retirement-crisis-coming-2013-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eweathering%20the%20subsequent%20financial%20fallout%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EToday%2C%20though%2C%20she%20and%20Karl%20are%20happily%20living%20in%20Ecuador%2C%20with%20a%20retirement%20nest%20egg%20that's%20only%20growing.%20It's%20an%20option%20that's%20become%20increasingly%20enticing%20to%20some%20older%20Americans%2C%20who%20are%20finding%20that%20their%20retirement%20funds%20go%20further%20abroad%20and%20that%20thriving%20ex-pat%20communities%20%E2%80%94%20alongside%20cheaper%20and%20more%20accessible%20healthcare%20%E2%80%94%20create%20a%20version%20of%20a%20comfortable%20retirement%20that%20the%20US%20has%20failed%20to%20deliver%20on.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20have%20more%20in%20savings%20now%20than%20we%20left%20with%2C%20and%20that's%20living%20a%20very%20nice%20lifestyle%2C%20traveling%20all%20over%20the%20world%2C%20and%20not%20having%20to%20scrimp%20or%20save%20at%20all%2C%26quot%3B%20Karl%20said.%20%26quot%3BSo%20it%20is%20the%20best%20of%20all%20worlds.%20It's%20a%20wonderful%2C%20wonderful%20place%20to%20live.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%229d2bfdf3-844c-4c2a-94fd-235523bee977%5C%22%3EPros%20and%20cons%20of%20moving%20abroad%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20decision%20to%20pack%20up%20two%20entire%20lives%20isn't%20always%20an%20easy%20one.%20Karl%20said%20that%20ex-pats%20need%20to%20adjust%20to%20a%20new%20reality%3A%20Don't%20expect%20to%20find%20the%20usual%20big%20box%20stores%20or%20even%20own%20a%20car.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20can't%20buy%20everything%20in%20one%20place%2C%20but%20it's%20more%20of%20a%20European%20style%20of%20shopping%2C%26quot%3B%20Karl%20said.%20Other%20cultural%20differences%20may%20prove%20daunting%20for%20some%3B%20Karl%20said%20it's%20important%20for%20people%20to%20learn%20at%20least%20a%20%26quot%3Bpassable%26quot%3B%20level%20of%20Spanish%20out%20of%20courtesy%20to%20the%20locals%2C%20and%20to%20make%20their%20experiences%20easier.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIndeed%2C%20moving%20abroad%20can%20present%20new%20logistical%20and%20cultural%20challenges%20for%20both%20movers%20and%20locals.%20New%20residents%20have%20to%20adapt%20to%20a%20new%20way%20of%20living%2C%20and%20often%20new%20systems%20of%20infrastructure%2C%20healthcare%2C%20and%20taxes%3B%20at%20the%20same%20time%2C%20locals%20might%20feel%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famericans-moving-abroad-cost-of-living-too-expensive-debt-retirement-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eripple%20effect%20of%20wealthier%20ex-pats%20driving%20up%20prices%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20for%20Karl%20and%20Brenda%2C%20the%20pros%20of%20making%20the%20move%20far%20outweigh%20the%20cons.%20The%20healthcare%20in%20Ecuador%20is%20%26quot%3Bwonderful%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20Karl%20said%20that%20they%20can't%20praise%20the%20medical%20facilities%20there%20enough.%20In%20fact%2C%20he%20said%20that%20the%20area%20is%20becoming%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmedical-tourism-americans-save-money-healthcare-2018-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emedical%20and%20dental%20vacation%20spot%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20where%20Americans%20come%20for%20cheaper%20elective%20procedures.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBrenda%20has%20been%20amazed%20by%20their%20experience%20with%20the%20medical%20system%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ein%20Ecuador.%20A%20few%20years%20back%2C%20she%20was%20in%20and%20out%20of%20the%20hospital%20for%20a%20few%20months%2C%20which%20amounted%20to%20about%20five%20trips%20to%20the%20emergency%20room%20and%20three%20surgeries.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOur%20total%20bill%20on%20our%20food%2C%20our%20room%2C%20our%20surgery%2C%20our%20medicine%20was%20%2425%2C000.%20It%20would've%20been%20%24600%2C000%20in%20the%20States%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20big%20change%20from%20the%20states%3A%20Most%20retirees%20don't%20own%20a%20car%2C%20Karl%20said.%20Instead%2C%20they%20can%20get%20around%20the%20city%20in%20a%20%242.50%20taxi%2C%20or%20pay%20the%20%240.17%20senior%20fare%20for%20an%20aboveground%20tram.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20almost%20have%20to%20laugh%20at%20the%20savings%20that%20you%20can%20make%20and%20it's%20a%20nice%2C%20clean%2C%20safe%2C%20very%20efficient%20way%20to%20get%20around%20in%20town%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22685873a5-014e-40d4-b5d2-c0193c211787%5C%22%3EAmerican%20ex-pat%20communities%20are%20growing%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20American%20retirement%20dream%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-retirement-of-peak-boomers-could-affect-economy-social-security-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eincreasingly%20slipping%20away%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20many%20older%20workers%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fretirement-crisis-social-security-pensions-student-loan-debt-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehoping%20to%20hang%20up%20their%20hats%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Savings%20are%20dwindling%2C%20Social%20Security%20isn't%20enough%20to%20get%20by%2C%20and%20healthcare%20costs%20are%20racking%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKarl%20and%20Brenda%20are%20sitting%20content%20with%20their%20nest%20egg.%20They%20receive%20Social%20Security%2C%20and%20said%20that%20they%20have%20cashed%20everything%20else%20out%20into%20certificate%20of%20savings%20deposits%20in%20Ecuador%2C%20which%20earn%20a%20robust%20return%20rate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20of%20December%2