0Rochester%2C%20Buffalo%2C%20and%20Syracuse.%20While%20prices%20in%20the%20cities%20have%20been%20fairly%20volatile%20in%20recent%20years%2C%20since%20February%202023%2C%20home%20values%20have%20risen%20by%2048%25%20in%20Rochester%20and%20Syracuse%20and%2035%25%20in%20Buffalo.%20That%20crushes%20the%2014%25%20national%20average%20over%20that%20timeline%2C%20according%20to%20Redfin%20data.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20Meyer%20said%20it's%20difficult%20to%20predict%20whether%20these%20states%20will%20continue%20outperforming%20in%20the%20future%2C%20he%20said%20he%20likes%20their%20prospects%20over%20a%2010-to-20-year%20time%20horizon.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPart%20of%20Meyer's%20bullishness%20stems%20from%20the%20fact%20that%20Connecticut%20and%20western%20New%20York%20are%20fairly%20insulated%20from%20the%20impacts%20of%20the%20climate%20crisis%20relative%20to%20other%20states%2C%20especially%20those%20in%20the%20south%20with%20more%20exposure%20to%20heat%20and%20severe%20storms.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPlus%2C%20he's%20skeptical%20that%20the%20migration%20from%20Northeastern%20and%20West%20Coast%20cities%20to%20southern%20states%20during%20the%20pandemic%20can%20keep%20going.%20Areas%20like%20western%20New%20York%20and%20the%20Midwest%20have%20excess%20infrastructure%2C%20he%20said%2C%20while%20places%20like%20Florida%20have%20struggled%20with%20the%20influx%20of%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%228ea6bed7-8d54-4e11-90ca-62e07ce97cd3%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E3%20states%20where%20appreciation%20is%20being%20stifled%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20New%20York%20and%20Connecticut%20might%20be%20among%20the%20areas%20less%20vulnerable%20to%20the%20climate%20crisis%20going%20forward%2C%20states%20in%20the%20south%20are%20more%20likely%20to%20be%20impacted.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThree%20states%20that%20are%20particularly%20susceptible%20to%20more%20extreme%20weather%20are%20Florida%2C%20Texas%2C%20and%20Louisiana%2C%20and%20home%20values%20feeling%20the%20brunt%20of%20this%20reality%2C%20Meyer%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20because%20of%20expensive%20insurance%20premiums%2C%20Meyer%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMajor%20carriers%20are%20pulling%20out%20of%20the%20market%2C%20and%20for%20many%20homeowners%2C%20the%20premiums%20are%20just%20unaffordable%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20numbers%20back%20up%20Meyer's%20argument.%20Home%20price%20growth%20over%20the%20last%2012%20months%20was%202.3%25%20in%20Florida%2C%20-1.1%25%20in%20Texas%2C%20and%202.2%25%20in%20Louisiana%2C%20according%20to%20Redfin%20data.%20Again%2C%20the%20national%20average%20was%204%25%20growth%20over%20the%20last%2012%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20insurance%20premiums%20front%2C%20the%20data%20is%20also%20there.%20According%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bankrate.com%2Finsurance%2Fhomeowners-insurance%2Fstates%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBankrate%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20national%20average%20premium%20is%20%242%2C270%20per%20year%20for%20a%20%24300%2C000%20home.%20But%20in%20Florida%2C%20the%20average%20is%20%245%2C531%20per%20year%3B%20in%20Louisiana%2C%20it's%20%244%2C296%3B%20and%20in%20Texas%2C%20it's%20%243%2C898.%20In%20New%20York%20and%20Connecticut%2C%20by%20comparison%2C%20annual%20average%20premiums%20are%20%241%2C733%20and%20%241%2C698%2C%20respectively.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-housing-markets-most-at-risk-climate-change-homeowners-insurance-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erecent%20study%20from%20Bankrate%3C%2Fa%3E%20found%20that%20average%20annual%20premiums%20in%20Miami%20are%20the%20highest%20in%20the%20country%20at%20%2410%2C473.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20housing%20economists%20and%20investors%20are%20starting%20to%20warn%20of%20the%20impacts%20of%20climate%20change%20on%20property%20values.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freal-estate-housing-market-climate-change-outlook-pre