g%20flat%20because%20they%20weren%E2%80%99t%20used%20to%20seeing%20someone%20like%20me%20go%20up%20to%20a%20stage%20to%20perform%20comedy%20before%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20notes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20tackle%20this%2C%20Sweta%20eases%20her%20anxiety%20by%20making%20light%20of%20her%20struggle%20to%20get%20on%20stage.%20If%20the%20steps%20are%20particularly%20steep%20and%20it%20takes%20time%20to%20climb%2C%20she%20jokes%2C%20%E2%80%9COh%2C%20thanks%20for%20clapping%20for%20two%20hundred%20years%2C%20guys!%E2%80%9D%20or%20%E2%80%9CI%E2%80%99m%20the%20disabled%20one%20here%20%E2%80%94%20what%E2%80%99s%20wrong%20with%20you%2C%20why%20did%20you%20stop%20clapping%3F%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESometimes%2C%20she%20even%20references%20a%20popular%20meme%20from%20the%202006%20film%20%3Cem%3EVivah%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20saying%2C%20%E2%80%9C%3Cem%3EJal%20lijiye%2C%20thak%20gaye%20honge%20clap%20karte%20karte%3C%2Fem%3E.%E2%80%9D%20She%20adds%2C%20%E2%80%9CIf%20the%20audience%20sees%20me%20struggling%20due%20to%20the%20infrastructure%2C%20I%20have%20to%20address%20it.%20If%20I%20don%E2%80%99t%2C%20it%20impacts%20my%20performance.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EChoosing%20to%20perform%20stand-up%20comedy%20is%20in%20itself%20a%20rebellious%20act%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20term%20%E2%80%98stand-up%E2%80%99%20in%20stand-up%20comedy%20could%20be%20seen%20as%20somewhat%20ableist%2C%20particularly%20from%20a%20disability-focused%20perspective%2C%E2%80%9D%20Sweta%20muses.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20typical%20image%20of%20a%20stand-up%20comedian%20involves%20a%20performer%20standing%20on%20stage%2C%20which%20can%20be%20at%20odds%20with%20the%20accessibility-centred%20narrative%20we%20strive%20for%20today.%20Generally%2C%20people%20with%20disabilities%20are%20imagined%20working%20from%20home%20or%2C%20if%20they%E2%80%99re%20comedians%2C%20performing%20on%20Zoom%20or%20writing%20funny%20blogs.%20Choosing%20to%20perform%20stand-up%20comedy%20in%20person%20is%20in%20itself%20a%20rebellious%20act%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20points%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBeing%20the%20only%20Indian%20stand-up%20comedian%20with%20spina%20bifida%20has%20made%20Sweta%20aware%20that%20her%20comedy%20has%20a%20deeper%20purpose%3A%20to%20shed%20light%20on%20the%20issues%20confronting%20people%20with%20disabilities%20and%20to%20ask%20her%20audience%20to%20think%20more%20deeply.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Mandar%20Latkar%2C%20a%20peer%20in%20the%20stand-up%20comedy%20scene%20who%20has%20witnessed%20her%20craft%20up%20close%2C%20Sweta%20excels%20at%20addressing%20tough%20issues%20with%20humour.%20%E2%80%9CSweta%20boldly%20addresses%20challenging%20themes%2C%20including%20her%20personal%20experiences%2C%E2%80%9D%20adding%20that%20she%E2%80%99s%20not%20afraid%20to%20confront%20topics%20that%20might%20have%20once%20been%20uncomfortable%20for%20her.%20He%20also%20highlights%20that%20Sweta%20wraps%20up%20her%20comedy%20sets%20with%20a%20segment%20focused%20on%20educating%20the%20audience%20about%20disability%20and%20correcting%20common%20misconceptions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20asked%20if%20she%20believes%20her%20voice%20has%20changed%20over%20the%20years%20to%20better%20connect%20with%20her%20audiences%2C%20she%20responds%2C%20%E2%80%9CI%20don%E2%80%99t%20think%20my%20voice%20has%20changed%20dramatically.%E2%80%9D%20Sweta%20remains%20committed%20to%20her%20voice%20but%20has%20refined%20how%20she%20discusses%20her%20experiences.%20%E2%80%9CChoosing%20not%20to%20talk%20about%20certain%20things%20has%20never%20been%20an%20option%20for%20me%2C%20and%20it%20never%20will%20be%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20states%20firmly.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20she%E2%80%99s%20not%20writing%20comedy%2C%20Sweta%20finds%20meaning%20in%20her%20advocacy%20work%20for%20individuals%20with%20disabilities.%20Why%20does%20she%20do%20it%3F%20%E2%80%9CBecause%20disability%20isn%E2%80%99t%20the%20problem%2C%20accessibility%2C%20or%20the%20lack%20of%20it%2C%20is%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F08%2FUntitled-design-20_11zon-1723471221.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%E2%80%9CChoosing%20not%20to%20talk%20about%20certain%20things%20has%20never%20been%20an%20option%20for%20me%2C%20and%20it%20never%20will%20be%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F08%2FUntitled-design-20_11zon-1723471221.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F08%2FUntitled-design-20_11zon-1723471221-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F08%2FUntitled-design-20_11zon-1723471221-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F08%2FUntitled-design-20_11zon-1723471221-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F08%2FUntitled-design-20_11zon-1723471221-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-360958%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3E%E2%80%9CChoosing%20not%20to%20talk%20about%20certain%20things%20has%20never%20been%20an%20option%20for%20me%2C%20and%20it%20never%20will%20be%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20during%20her%20school%20years%20that%20Sweta%20first%20realised%20how%20unaccommodating%20society%20could%20be%20towards%20people%20like%20her.%20She%20vividly%20recalls%20a%20moment%20when%20a%20teacher%20allowed%20all%20the%20other%20children%20to%20play%20outside%20but%20told%20her%20to%20stay%20in%20the%20classroom.%20%E2%80%9CEven%20my%20parents%20let%20me%20join%20the%20other%20children%20in%20our%20housing%20colony%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20rues.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20completing%20her%20postgraduate%20studies%20at%20Symbiosis%20Institute%20for%20Media%20and%20Communications%20in%20Pune%2C%20Sweta%20was%20offered%20a%20position%20at%20Blue%20Lotus%20Communications%2C%20a%20PR%20agency%20in%20Mumbai.%20Her%20parents%20were%20hesitant%20about%20her%20relocating%2C%20but%20her%20boss%20made%20a%20special%20trip%20to%20Pune%20to%20convince%20them.%20Although%20she%20moved%20to%20Mumbai%2C%20the%20travelling%20in%20monsoon%20became%20too%20tiring%2C%20prompting%20her%20to%20return%20to%20Pune%2C%20and%20she%20ultimately%20decided%20to%20quit.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWhen%20I%20first%20moved%20to%20Mumbai%20for%20work%2C%20it%20took%20me%20two%20months%20to%20find%20a%20hostel%20with%20a%20lift%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20recalls.%20It%20was%20during%20this%20period%20that%20she%20became%20resolute%20in%20her%20goal%20to%20bring%20attention%20to%20the%20challenges%20faced%20by%20people%20like%20herself.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EUsing%20her%20voice%20to%20push%20for%20greater%20accessibility%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESweta%20shares%20that%20her%20parents%20have%20always%20motivated%20her%20to%20use%20her%20voice%20for%20change.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDuring%20a%20trip%20to%20Rajasthan%20in%202007%2C%20she%20was%20amazed%20to%20find%20Western-style%20toilets%20even%20at%20small%20highway%20%3Cem%3Edhabas%3C%2Fem%3E.%20When%20she%20asked%20why%2C%20the%20owners%20said%20it%20was%20for%20expats.%20She%20wondered%3A%20if%20the%20Government%20can%20be%20so%20accommodating%20to%20expats%2C%20why%20can%E2%80%99t%20they%20do%20the%20same%20for%20people%20with%20disabilities%3F%20As%20a%2020-year-old%2C%20she%20was%20infuriated.%20%E2%80%9CMy%20parents%20encouraged%20me%20to%20write%20to%20the%20Prime%20Minister%20or%20the%20Chief%20Minister%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20recalls%20with%20a%20smile.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20her%20earliest%20initiatives%20was%20a%20project%20called%20%E2%80%98Give%20Some%20Space%E2%80%99%2C%20which%20she%20launched%20with%20her%20friend%20Vishal%20Sawvaant%2C%20a%20wheelchair%20user.%20Together%2C%20they%20installed%20ramps%20on%20SB%20Road%2C%20Fergusson%20College%20Road%2C%20and%20nearby%20areas%20in%20Pune%2C%20making%20it%20easier%20for%20wheelchair%20users%20to%20access%20bookstores%2C%20restaurants%2C%20and%20educational%20institutions.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20lived%20reality%20of%20wheelchair%20users%20is%20so%20ignored%20that%20they%20often%20don%E2%80%99t%20even%20have%20the%20option%20to%20visit%20a%20college%20to%20inquire%20about%20admission%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20points%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202017%2C%20Sweta%20and%20her%20cousin%20Nalini%20Mangwani%20created%20an%20art%20installation%20called%20the%20Restroom%20Project.%20The%20artwork%20depicted%20a%20map%20of%20restaurants%20in%20Pune%20on%20a%20cardboard%20canvas%20painted%20with%20bright%20blue%20strokes.%20The%20map%20included%20landmarks%20shaped%20like%20toilet%20seats%20to%20illustrate%20the%20challenges%20of%20finding%20disability-friendly%20restrooms.%20Opening%20each%20commode%20lid%20on%20the%20canvas%20revealed%20whether%20the%20restaurant%20was%20accessible%20by%20people%20with%20disabilities%2C%20whether%20there%20were%20steps%20to%20the%20restroom%20or%20other%20relevant%20features.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20asked%20about%20how%20she%20sees%20her%20comedy%20progressing%2C%20Sweta%20says%20that%20there%20are%20many%20aspects%20of%20her%20life%20that%20she%E2%80%99s%20yet%20to%20figure%20out%2C%20including%20nuances%20of%20living%20with%20a%20disability.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20definitely%20want%20to%20talk%20more%20about%20the%20role%20that%20upbringing%20and%20conditioning%20play%20in%20the%20context%20of%20people%E2%80%99s%20perception%20of%20people%20with%20disabilities.%20Sometimes%2C%20even%20after%20seeing%20me%20on%20stage%2C%20people%20still%20believe%20that%20those%20with%20disabilities%20should%20stay%20quiet%20and%20not%20talk%20about%20their%20challenges%2C%E2%80%9D